==>OBSERVATION: Burned Down Shack
Wisps of steam rise off of the charred timbers of what was once a fair-sized building. Small flames flare up occasionally producing a deep crackling sound. Paper-thin pieces of ash float hither and yon. An odd-shaped sign lies on the ground.

George is here staring at the charred remains of his gum factory.

There is a brass key hanging on George's belt.

You can also see a leather-bound book, a cauldron (in which is some metallic flakes) and a burned sketch here.
