Almost to the Top, On the Derrick
You are just a few feet from the top of the derrick. One of the adjacent slats has the following painted on it:

"I'm Black, I'm Brown,
Yellow and Clear;
I'm often found
Amongst the Gears.

Found Above
And in the Ground,
I can ease a
Grating Sound.
What am I?"

There is a candle here wedged between a couple of pieces of wood.
